The paper proposes a framework for on-device machine learning with privacy preservation, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses privacy preservation techniques, which suggests that it could belong to the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The use of a multi-hop protocol for over-the-air transmission of seed samples could also suggest that it belongs to the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper proposes a generative model for data augmentation, which could suggest that it belongs to the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of compression on communication payload, which could suggest that it belongs to the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
